OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 26 Apr to Tue 5 May
OL,6,FHigh pressure is likely to be centred
OL,7,Fclose to or over the UK through much
OL,8,Fof the period. Therefore, many places
OL,9,Fwill be largely dry with some clear or
OL,10,Fsunny spells, although there may be
OL,11,Fsome overnight mist and fog patches.
OL,12,FThere could, however, be some
OL,13,Foutbreaks of rain or showers at times,
OL,14,Fespecially in the west and northwest.
OL,15,FWinds will be mostly light, but may be
OL,16,Ffresher around the coasts at times.
OL,17,FTemperatures will generally be near to
OL,18,For a little above normal, but there
OL,19,Fmay be some colder conditions at first
OL,20,Fin the far northeast. Towards the end
OL,21,Fof the period there is a chance that
OL,22,Fconditions turn a little more
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Funsettled.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1776784268
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 6 May to Wed 20 May
OL,6,FResidual high pressure will likely
OL,7,Fgive way to more unsettled conditions
OL,8,Fthrough the early part of the period.
OL,9,FThis will probably allow Atlantic low
OL,10,Fpressure systems to spread towards the
OL,11,FUK, increasing the chance of periods
OL,12,Fof heavy rain and perhaps strong winds
OL,13,Fat times. Towards the middle of the
OL,14,Fmonth, weather patterns become
OL,15,Fincreasingly uncertain; however, the
OL,16,Fwettest and windiest conditions seem
OL,17,Fmost likely to be in the northwest,
OL,18,Fwith the drier and more settled
OL,19,Fconditions in the southeast.
OL,20,FTemperatures will likely be near
OL,21,Fnormal.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
